Refined sugar, like the kind found in sweets, chocolate, biscuits, can cause acneAlthough antibiotics usually by kills the bacteria causing the spots, the medication also kills all the “friendly” bacteria that live in your gut Sugar is worse than you think 

As numerous clinical studies have shown, people with acne do not process sugar well in their bodies. Refined sugar, like the kind found in sweets, chocolate, biscuits, can cause acne. But notice that I use the word “can” and not “will. Refined sugar is often thought of as inflammatory and fresh fruits and vegetables, anti-inflammatory. Get the balance right, and you can carry on eating your favourite chocolate. 



