Antibiotics do more harm than good 

If you go to a doctor complaining about acne, chances are you’ll be prescribed antibiotics to calm your inflamed skin. Although this usually does the trick by killing the bacteria causing the spots, the medication also kills all the “friendly” bacteria that live in your gut.  

Without these “friendly” bacteria to protect you, when you eventually do come off the medication, “unfriendly” bacteria start to overgrow in the gut. Not only do they release toxins, they also create other problems, including - wait for it –acne! So off you go to get another course of antibiotics, and so long as you keep taking them, your skin will be OK.  

If the catch-22 situation you’re in, I suggest taking a nutritional supplement called a probiotic for a few weeks. Probiotics are designed to replenish the “friendly” bacteria in your gut and in turn, help solve your skin problems. 

 

